    "Eating disorders (anorexia nervosa, bulimia nervosa, binge eating disorder) frequently co-occur with substance use disorders, with approximately 50% of individuals with eating disorders also having SUD. Both conditions involve loss of control over behavior, distorted thinking, and disruption of reward circuitry. Stimulants and appetite suppressants may be used to facilitate weight loss, while alcohol and cannabis may be used to manage emotional distress or facilitate binge eating.",
